The paper proposes a method for learning an embedding space over the domain of network architectures to enable the selection of architectures for evaluation during compressed architecture search. This involves using Bayesian Optimization with a kernel function defined over the proposed embedding space. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing)
- cs.SY (Systems and Control)
